api-help-flags:
{{optional}} Label for the API help flags box

Parameters:
* $1 - Number of flags to be displayed
api-help-flag-deprecated: Flag displayed for an API module that is deprecated
api-help-flag-internal: Flag displayed for an API module that is considered internal or unstable
api-help-flag-readrights: Flag displayed for an API module that requires read rights
api-help-flag-writerights: Flag displayed for an API module that requires write rights

Used to indicate that one of the possible values in the list is the empty string.

* $1 - Number of items in the rest of the list; may be 0
* $2 - Remainder of the list as a comma-separated string
api-help-param-limit:
Used to display the maximum value of a limit parameter

Parameters:
* $1 - Maximum value

Used to display the maximum values of a limit parameter

Parameters:
* $1 - Maximum value without the apihighlimits right
* $2 - Maximum value with the apihighlimits right
api-help-param-integer-min:
Used to display an integer parameter with a minimum but no maximum value

Parameters:
* $1 - 1 if the parameter takes one value, 2 if the parameter takes any number of values
* $2 - Minimum value
* $3 - unused

See also:
* {{msg-mw|api-help-param-integer-max}}
* {{msg-mw|api-help-param-integer-minmax}}
api-help-param-integer-max:
Used to display an integer parameter with a maximum but no minimum value.

Parameters:
* $1 - 1 if the parameter takes one value, 2 if the parameter takes any number of values
* $2 - (Unused)
* $3 - Maximum value
See also:
* {{msg-mw|Api-help-param-integer-min}}
* {{msg-mw|Api-help-param-integer-minmax}}
api-help-param-integer-minmax:
Used to display an integer parameter with a maximum and minimum values

Parameters:
* $1 - 1 if the parameter takes one value, 2 if the parameter takes any number of values
* $2 - Minimum value
* $3 - Maximum value

* {{msg-mw|api-help-param-integer-min}}
* {{msg-mw|api-help-param-integer-max}}
